{
  "document_id": "isa-28",
  "title": "Isaiah 28",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Woe to the proud garland of the drunkards of Ephraim"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "See, the Lord has one who is mighty and strong,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Trampled under foot will be"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "And the fading flower of its glorious beauty,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "On that day the Lord of hosts will be a garland of glory"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "and a spirit of justice to the one who sits in judgment"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "These also reel with wine"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "All tables are covered with filthy vomit;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“Whom will he teach knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "For it is precept upon precept, precept upon precept,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Truly, with stammering lip"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "to whom he has said,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Therefore the word of the Lord will be to them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Therefore hear the word of the Lord, you scoffers"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Because you have said, “We have made a covenant with death,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "therefore thus says the Lord God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "And I will make justice the line"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Then your covenant with death will be annulled,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "As often as it passes through, it will take you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "For the bed is too short to stretch oneself on it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "For the Lord will rise up as on Mount Perazim;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Now therefore do not scoff,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Listen and hear my voice;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Do those who plow for sowing plow continually?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "When they have leveled its surface,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "For they are well instructed;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "For dill is not threshed with a threshing sledge,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Grain is crushed for bread,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "isa-28-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "This also comes from the Lord of hosts;"
    }
  ]
}